{"lemma":"مَضَرّاتُ","slug":"مَضَرّاتُ","root":"ض.ر.ر","root_slug":"ض-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25685","n38669"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"harm"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of مُضِرّ (muḍirr)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of ضَرَّ (ḍarra, “to damage”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ma.dˤar.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25685","headword_ar":"مَضَرَّةٌ","root":"Dr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cause,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means, of harm, injury, hurt, mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"damage; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manofaEapN","text_ar":"مَنْفَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) [and simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harm, injury, hurt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DararN","text_ar":"ضَرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaAr~u","text_ar":"مَضَارُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n38669","headword_ar":"مضّرهُ","root":"mDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamoDiyrN","text_ar":"تَمْضِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He referred his lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin, to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDar","text_ar":"مُضَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mudar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the ancestor of most of the Arabs who trace up their genealogy to Ismá'eel, or Ishmael]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to be of the race of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDar","text_ar":"مُضَر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by referring his lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin, to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)       -A2-  It is said, of the race of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDar","text_ar":"مُضَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mD~rhA All~`h fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"مضّرها اللّٰه فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make them to be in the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of hell]; the verb being derived from their name: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God collect them together"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jan~ada Aljunuwda","text_ar":"جَنَّدَ الجُنُودَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Z, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroy them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) from the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba damuhu xiDorFA miDorFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ دَمُهُ خِضْرًا مِضْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the first of the senses explained below: (TA:) J says, [in the S,] that its origin seems to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDuwru All~abani","text_ar":"مُضُورُ اللَّبَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ the biting of the tongue by milk, ” and that it is with teshdeed to denote muchness, or intensiveness. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Z"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}